section.section:
In addition to paragraph (1) of this subsection, it is a violation of this subtitle, if the Commissioner, in consultation with an independent review organization, medical expert, the Department, or other appropriate entity, determines that the criteria and standards used by a health maintenance organization to conduct utilization review are not:
objective;
clinically valid;
compatible with established principles of health care; or
flexible enough to allow deviations from norms when justified on a case by case basis.
